CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 26,1957, page1. reads: "Church Target - spokesman for Ebenezer Baptist Church say the are opposed to a liquor license being issued to Lou Jules' 88 Bar, at 2037 Centre Avenue because the establishment is within 300 feet of Ebenezer Baptist Property. --Teenie Harris"
TitMainTitle: C. G. Nickens, M.D. office at 2035 Centre Avenue, Lou and Jules Uptown 88 Bar at 2037 Centre Avenue, Hirsch Cleaners and Tailors, and Sigal's Household Supplies, Hill District
